> @daall: It looks like the new vsimage test didn't run on this PR?

Correct! At least for today (and maybe also tomorrow depending on how things go) I have it set up to only run if the PR has a "Jenkins-Pilot" label on it so we can keep an eye on it. We can do that for this PR.

@daall: I don't think GitHub will add PR test builds after the PR has already been opened. If you're currently flagging the test based on the "Jenkins-Pilot" label, I would guess that the label would need to be present at the time the PR is opened for the test to get added.

> @daall: I don't think it will add PR test builds after the PR has already been opened. If you're currently flagging the test based on the "Jenkins-Pilot" label, I would guess that the label would need to be present at the time the PR is opened for the test to get added.

Tamer and I were able to run the tests on our PRs by adding the label and pushing/commenting afterwards, I'm not sure why it's not working for this PR at the moment. I'm guessing there is some delay between adding the label and it showing up in the github API?

chatted with xin, it looks like I need to add `--log-file-level debug` option

Before this change, the configuration "log_path" in ansible/ansible.cfg will trigger some ansible code to set the logging level of root logger to INFO.

This changed removed the "log_path" configuration. Level of root logger will be default WARNING. That's why after this change, we need to use the `--log-file-level` option to explicitly set logging level.
